9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 191, L.D. 291, “An Act to Eliminate the
10 Lodging Tax on Campground Sites and Revert to Using the Current Sales Tax”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§2-F is enacted to read:
14 2-F. Campground. "Campground" has the same meaning as in Title 22, section 2491,
15 subsection 1.
16 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§2-G is enacted to read:
17 2-G. Campground accommodation. "Campground accommodation" means an
18 accommodation offered to the public for consideration and includes cabins, tents or other
19 structures that may be provided by a campground to occupants for sleeping purposes. It
20 does not include bare land or land on which a customer may pitch a tent or park a camper
21 trailer, motor home or truck camper.
22 Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§2-H is enacted to read:
23 2-H. Campground site. "Campground site" means bare land or land on which a
24 person may pitch a tent or park a camper trailer, motor home or truck camper regardless of
25 whether a hookup is provided.
26 Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§6 is amended to read:
27 6. Living quarters. "Living quarters" means sleeping rooms, sleeping or
28 housekeeping accommodations, and tent or trailer space or campground accommodations.
29 Sec. 5. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§11-B, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 375, Pt. A, §1, is
30 amended to read:
31 11-B. Room remarketer. "Room remarketer" means a person who reserves, arranges
32 for, offers, furnishes or collects or receives consideration for the rental of living quarters or
33 the rental of a campground site in this State, whether directly or indirectly, pursuant to a
