19 Sec. 16. Application. This Act applies to sales occurring on or after January 1, 2026.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment strikes the bill and, beginning January 1, 2026, excludes the rental of
2244 a campground site from the lodging tax of 9%, instead making the rental of a campground
2255 site subject to the general sales tax rate, currently 5.5%. A campground site is defined as
2266 bare land or land on which a person may pitch a tent or park a camper trailer, motor home
2277 or truck camper, regardless of whether a hookup is provided.
